  "text": "We ran JeDi using present-day climate data [CITATION_1] for the period between 1960 and 1989. We looped over these 30 years of climate re-analysis until we reached 120 years, which is a sufficiently long time for the model to reach a steady-state [CITATION_2] . In the following, these results are referred to as JeDi present-day simulation.",
